To test Hypothesis 2d, a two-way ANCOVA (Eq. 4) was performed to investigate the effects of the three classes of pachinko parlours (always closed, always open, opened-then-closed) and the four radii (0.5 km, 0.5–1 km, 1–5 km, 5–10 km radii of pachinko parlours) on outcome variables (daily income-generating crime rate per 100 km square) with control variables (years when the income-generating crime occurred and the number of convenience stores and always open pachinko parlours near pachinko parlours). Tukey’s honest significant difference test was conducted [59]. In Eq. 4, Y is the year when the crime occurred, β3 is the coefficient, and l is 7 years (from 2017 to 2023). The other variables in Eq. 4 are the same as those in Eqs. 1, 2, and 3.4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
